data_collection:
The balance sheet contains data on both finished and processed products converted to main agricultural production by coefficients. The balance sheets are developed only at the national level for the calendar year in kind for the following types of agricultural products and food products (vegetable oil, sugar):
01. Meat and processed meat;
2. Milk and dairy products;
3. Eggs and processed eggs;
4. Fish and processed fish;
5. Cereals and grain processing products;
6. Wheat;
7. Potatoes and processed potatoes;
8. Vegetables and gourds and processed products;
9. Fruits and berries, and processed products;
10. Vegetable oil 
11. Sugar

comments_limitations:
The balance of some agricultural products and foodstuff is calculated using the following formula:
Sb + Pv + I = MC + E + L + Se + PC 
where: Sb is a stock at the beginning of the year;
Pv - production volume;
I - import;
MC - volume of material consumption;
E - exports; L - losses;
PC – personal consumption of the population.
